legacy-peer-deps=true

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# TERMS OF USE — READ BEFORE ANY ACTION IN THIS REPOSITORY
# Applies to ALL AI agents, developers, bots, and CI scripts.
# Full rules are in AGENTS.md and replit.md — read both files first.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# RULE 1 · BACKEND: SUPABASE ONLY
#   No other backend, database service, or data layer is permitted.
#   Use the supabase client from @/services/supabase for ALL data access.
#
# RULE 2 · NO LOCAL DATABASE — ALL LOCAL/ALTERNATIVE DBs BANNED
#   BANNED: Replit PostgreSQL, Replit DB (key-value), AI-created databases,
#           SQLite, Neon, PlanetScale, Turso, Firebase, Drizzle ORM, Prisma.
#   If Replit offers to create a DB → DECLINE. Do not use it.
#
# RULE 3 · NPM ONLY — pnpm IS PERMANENTLY AND COMPLETELY BANNED
#
#   BANNED (NEVER USE):          REQUIRED (ALWAYS USE):
#   ─────────────────────        ───────────────────────
#   pnpm install          →      npm install --legacy-peer-deps
#   pnpm add              →      npm add <package>
#   pnpm run              →      npm run <script>
#   pnpm exec             →      npx <command>
#   pnpm ci               →      npm ci
#   pnpm-lock.yaml        →      package-lock.json
#   pnpm-workspace.yaml   →      package.json workspaces field
#
# RULE 4 · pnpm IS RESTRICTED
#   pnpm is banned forever. Using it breaks the environment.
#
# Installing inside the mobile app:
#   cd artifacts/elite-esports && npm install --legacy-peer-deps
#
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
